interface towards other control objects -The Control Object shall have a
unique numbering in WBS -Status (S1-S4) defined by check lists, -Mapped
to level 5 control object schedule for schedule follow-up -Mapped to
Civil Construction PO/Contracts -Mapped to Contractors Work Packages
-Mapped to BoQ/Cost WBS -Mapped to Climate Budget (klimabudsjett)
-Mapped to deliverables list for at latest at status $4 for control
objects -The natural level to perform Design Check and Approvals -Approx
the same level as a DD-drawing`,
  },
  {
    title: "4 Model object",
    text: `4. Model object: is the lowest level of modelled shapes in the 3D model.
Can be picked from libraries or created directly in 3D model. Control
objects often consist of several model objects. Status ($1-S4) is not
set on model object level, but on control object level.`,
  },
];
---

<style>
  .container {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 300px;
    /* background-color: rgb(115, 255, 0); */
  }

  /* Make the image to responsive */
  .image {
    width: 50%;
    height: 600px;
    background-color: rgb(255, 146, 5);
  }

  /* The overlay effect - lays on top of the container and over the image */
  .overlay {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    backdrop-filter: darken(0.6);
    /* background: rgb(0, 0, 0); */
    color: #f1f1f1;
    width: 100%;
    transition: 0.5s ease;
    opacity: 0;
    color: white;
    font-size: 20px;
    padding: 20px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  /* When you mouse over the container, fade in the overlay title */
  .container:hover .overlay {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  #page {
    display: grid;
    width: 100%;
    /* height: 800px; */
    grid-template-areas:
      "tri tri  text"
      "tri  tri text"
      "img  img img";
    grid-template-rows: 1fr 1fr 200px;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
  }

  #page > .text {
    grid-area: text;
    /* background-color: #8ca0ff; */
    background-color: #4c94c4;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
  }

  #page > .tri {
    grid-area: tri;
    background-color: #ffa08c;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    /* display: grid; */
    /* place-items: center; */
  }

  #page > .img {
    grid-area: img;
    background-color: #8cffa0;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
    /* background-color: #f3f3f3; */
  }
  .triangle {
    color: #fcac62;
    transition: color 0.4s ease-in-out, transform 0.2s ease-in-out;
  }
  .triangle:hover {
    color: #f1cdaa;
    box-shadow: 0px 8px 6px -5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.103);
  }
  .triangleSectionContainer {
    position: relative;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .triangleSectionContainer:hover {
    z-index: 5;
    transform: scale(1.1);
    transition: color 0.4s ease-in-out, transform 0.2s ease-in-out;
  }

  .triangleSectionContainer:hover .centered {
    color: rgb(255, 255, 255);
  }

  .centered {
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: scale(1) translate(-50%, -50%);
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 600;
    pointer-events: none;
    color: rgb(15, 15, 15);
    transition: 0.2s color ease-in-out;
  }
</style>
